20 fucking years.

52:48.232 --> 52:49.665
Are you out
of your mind, mark?

52:54.171 --> 52:55.804
Don't you realize...

52:55.806 --> 52:58.541
That every guy
that works here,
including myself,

52:58.543 --> 53:00.876
would have quit
a long time ago, man,

53:00.878 --> 53:02.845
if they didn't
respect you, okay?

53:02.847 --> 53:04.313
Mark, listen to me!

53:05.348 --> 53:07.583
Mark.

53:07.585 --> 53:10.519
They believe you,

53:10.521 --> 53:11.921
not like
your father,

53:11.923 --> 53:13.789
who they know
don't give a shit
about them,

53:13.791 --> 53:15.658
'cause they know
deep down inside
that you care,

53:15.660 --> 53:17.459
and you go and you
pull this shit.

53:17.461 --> 53:19.628
Bullshit, Boyd!

53:19.630 --> 53:21.797
Most of these guys
are here because we have

53:21.799 --> 53:23.966
the best payment plan
in the city. That's it.

53:23.968 --> 53:26.502
You see
any of them have my back
in this morning's meeting

53:26.504 --> 53:28.537
until I told them
how much money
they stood to make?

53:28.539 --> 53:31.340
Speaking of,
are they actually gonna
get paid on Monday,

53:31.342 --> 53:33.642
or was that just
some more bullshit that
you're saying, mark?

53:33.644 --> 53:36.679
Look, I don't like
how my father runs this place
any more than you do,

53:36.681 --> 53:37.846
but I have
a responsibility--

53:37.848 --> 53:39.481
no, listen to me!
Are they,

53:39.483 --> 53:41.283
or aren't they
gonna get paid, mark?

53:41.285 --> 53:42.518
Don't bullshit me.

53:44.221 --> 53:46.288
Don't fucking
bullshit me.

53:50.560 --> 53:51.760
Unbelievable, mark.

53:51.762 --> 53:53.896
Boyd, listen to me, okay?

53:53.898 --> 53:57.233
If we don't get
to 300 cars by 5:00 P.M. today,

53:57.235 --> 53:59.501
none of it is gonna matter,
anyway, all right?

53:59.503 --> 54:00.736
Because nothing
is gonna change.

54:02.305 --> 54:03.472
Okay.

54:03.474 --> 54:04.473
You're right.

54:04.475 --> 54:05.641
"Okay"?

54:05.643 --> 54:07.009
"Okay"?

54:07.011 --> 54:09.812
What, are you and I not
on the same page anymore?

54:11.581 --> 54:13.482
You know what?

54:13.484 --> 54:15.317
Go fuck yourself,
mark.

54:17.921 --> 54:20.322
Where do you think
you're going?

54:24.361 --> 54:25.461
Look here, mark.

54:25.463 --> 54:27.730
Look, you can lie
to the customer,

54:27.732 --> 54:29.999
and you
can lie to me,

54:30.001 --> 54:31.900
but you can't lie
to yourself, man.

54:31.902 --> 54:33.269
Mm.

54:33.271 --> 54:34.970
And I know you're
up in your head

54:34.972 --> 54:37.606
about your
new car dealership
and changing things,

54:37.608 --> 54:40.009
but the fact is...

54:41.745 --> 54:43.746
You're scared
of your old man,

54:43.748 --> 54:46.715
and that's
the reason
why Scott got fired.

55:11.641 --> 55:13.776
What?
Little problem
just showed up.

55:16.012 --> 55:17.479
Yo, boss.

55:21.051 --> 55:23.786
I need
to speak to the boss
right fucking now!

55:23.788 --> 55:25.321
You're not the owner,
are you? No.

55:25.323 --> 55:26.555
Shut it.
Mark: Excuse me.

55:26.557 --> 55:27.856
Excuse me.
You wanna watch
your mouth?

55:27.858 --> 55:29.458
Who the fuck are you?
I'm the owner.

55:29.460 --> 55:30.959
Oh, that's good.
I want to talk to you.

55:30.961 --> 55:33.395
You know what?
I bought a car here
last night from her.

55:33.397 --> 55:34.530
Yes, you did.
I don't want it.

55:34.532 --> 55:36.065
Well, that makes
two of us.

55:36.067 --> 55:38.500
I know my fucking rights,
so let's not play any games.

55:38.502 --> 55:40.602
No, let's not,
but first things first.

55:40.604 --> 55:43.572
You swear at me again, and i
will throw your fucking ass
right out of my store.

55:43.574 --> 55:45.507
Now, I was
about to go outside

55:45.509 --> 55:47.576
and get a free hot dog
and a coke.

55:47.578 --> 55:49.078
What do you say
you join me?

55:49.080 --> 55:51.046
If the price were right
on this one,

55:51.048 --> 55:53.582
would you be willing
to go colorblind?

55:53.584 --> 55:54.616
Like I told you
on the phone

55:54.618 --> 55:56.085
this morning,
Mr. Chamberlain,

55:56.087 --> 55:58.987
I'm looking
for dark graphite,
not arctic silver.

55:58.989 --> 56:01.056
And I can appreciate
that, sheri, but--

56:01.058 --> 56:03.726
I came to get the car
that I drove for more
than an hour to buy,

56:03.728 --> 56:06.061
a car, quite frankly,
I'm beginning to doubt
that you ever had.

56:06.063 --> 56:08.497
Sheri, I assure you,
it was here.

56:08.499 --> 56:11.066
I mean, I personally
put my hands on it just
moments after we spoke.

56:11.068 --> 56:12.368
Then where is it?

56:12.370 --> 56:14.837
Heh. That's a good question.

56:14.839 --> 56:16.839
Three-day consumer
right of refusal in Arizona

56:16.841 --> 56:18.974
applies only to sales
in which the seller

56:18.976 --> 56:20.676
solicits you
at your place of residence,

56:20.678 --> 56:22.144
and I didn't come
to your home, chief.

56:22.146 --> 56:23.979
You came to mine.

56:23.981 --> 56:26.048
Well, that's
not exactly what
my attorney told me.

56:26.050 --> 56:28.484
Well, then you
should fire him,
'cause he's wrong.

56:28.486 --> 56:29.852
You know, it really
doesn't matter, anyway,

56:29.854 --> 56:32.521
because you have
your own return policy.

56:32.523 --> 56:34.156
Wrong again.

56:34.158 --> 56:35.691
I have
an exchange policy.

56:35.693 --> 56:37.893
Does this look
like Walmart to you?

56:37.895 --> 56:39.695
And the answer may be,
you know, that it sold

56:39.697 --> 56:41.130
in the time it took you
to get here.

56:41.132 --> 56:42.564
That's not uncommon
in this business.

56:42.566 --> 56:44.733
And if that is
the case,

56:44.735 --> 56:47.069
I deeply apologize,

56:47.071 --> 56:50.439
and I will take
very good care of you...

56:50.441 --> 56:51.874
On one of these
arctic silvers.

56:51.876 --> 56:53.409
Like I told you--

56:53.411 --> 56:55.043
but before we
rush to judgment,

56:55.045 --> 56:57.446
let me check with
one of my managers.

56:57.448 --> 56:59.982
I mean, for all I know,
it was sent out for
a window tint or something.

56:59.984 --> 57:01.817
Yeah, right.
Okay.

57:01.819 --> 57:03.152
Let's head in.

57:03.154 --> 57:04.086
You want a hot dog?

57:04.088 --> 57:05.421
Vegetarian.

57:05.423 --> 57:06.522
Vegan hot dog?

57:06.524 --> 57:08.757
Hey, man,
don't patronize me.

57:08.759 --> 57:10.859
Then don't play stupid
with me, Mr. mcmillen.

57:10.861 --> 57:12.928
Come on, man.
You signed a contract.

57:12.930 --> 57:16.632
You can't just unwind
because your wife didn't
give you permission.

57:22.839 --> 57:25.941
Look, okay, I get it.

57:25.943 --> 57:28.677
You came in yesterday
without your wife,

57:28.679 --> 57:30.446
wanted to just look around,

57:30.448 --> 57:33.549
and then you happened to find
something that you liked.

57:33.551 --> 57:34.883
It's okay.

57:34.885 --> 57:36.885
Hey, it happens, all right?

57:36.887 --> 57:39.888
You're not the first,
and you're certainly
not gonna be the last.

57:39.890 --> 57:42.491
You know, this is why
people hate buying cars.

57:42.493 --> 57:43.692
Right, because
it's our fault

57:43.694 --> 57:45.160
that you made
a major purchase

57:45.162 --> 57:46.728
without talking
to your wife first.

57:46.730 --> 57:48.931
I can see how we'd
be to blame for that.

57:48.933 --> 57:50.098
Here. I'll tell you what.

57:50.100 --> 57:51.533
If it'll help
smooth things over,

57:51.535 --> 57:52.901
why don't you
have your wife call me?

57:52.903 --> 57:55.704
I'm serious.
Anytime, okay? Maybe--

57:55.706 --> 57:57.673
no, I don't think so.
Think I'm gonna call
the Attorney General.

57:57.675 --> 57:59.741
I think this is
a matter that he would
like to discuss.

57:59.743 --> 58:02.244
You know what?
That is a great idea.

58:02.246 --> 58:05.047
You should call him,
and when you get Gary
on the line,

58:05.049 --> 58:07.182
I want you to ask him
how Debra, his wife,
is doing

58:07.184 --> 58:09.585
and how she's
enjoying that new suburban
she's driving,

58:09.587 --> 58:12.020
you know, the one
she's borrowing from us.

58:12.022 --> 58:14.590
Mr. mcmillen,
you got a great car.

58:14.592 --> 58:16.091
Enjoy it.

58:18.528 --> 58:20.128
Want a hot dog?

58:22.198 --> 58:23.198
Nice work.

58:23.200 --> 58:24.800
I have my moments.

58:24.802 --> 58:26.668
Don't forget to hide
that idiot's trade-in.

58:26.670 --> 58:28.737
I don't want him
getting any bright ideas.

58:28.739 --> 58:31.940
I won't, just as long
as you don't forget
about your wife.

58:51.761 --> 58:53.295
I--
i go to sleep,

58:53.297 --> 58:54.897
you're not home.

58:54.899 --> 58:57.766
I get up,
you're already gone.

58:57.768 --> 58:59.301
And if we do manage
to share a word,

58:59.303 --> 59:00.903
it almost always ends
in a car deal.

59:02.705 --> 59:04.006
Okay.

59:05.942 --> 59:07.576
I...

59:07.578 --> 59:09.845
I hear you,
all right? I do.

59:09.847 --> 59:10.913
I'm listening, okay?

59:10.915 --> 59:13.649
But I really
need you to hear me.

59:13.651 --> 59:15.183
I need
one more day--

59:15.185 --> 59:17.119
okay, mark, this isn't
about one more day.

59:17.121 --> 59:19.187
This is about
what's best for you

59:19.189 --> 59:21.223
taking priority over anyone
or anything else.

59:21.225 --> 59:23.759
I mean, this is about
you choosing the store
above our marriage,

59:23.761 --> 59:25.627
and that
all doesn't change
with one more day.

59:25.629 --> 59:27.930
Ashley, I have been
working my ass off--

59:27.932 --> 59:30.699
you really think your dad's
just gonna suddenly up
and change his ways?

59:30.701 --> 59:32.834
No! But it
doesn't matter.

59:32.836 --> 59:34.102
Okay? It doesn't,

59:34.104 --> 59:36.204
because as soon
as I have my new store,

59:36.206 --> 59:38.574
you have no idea.
Everything is gonna
change for us, okay--

59:38.576 --> 59:40.709
mark, that's the problem.

59:42.145 --> 59:44.746
The new store
shouldn't be the catalyst

59:44.748 --> 59:46.615
for things being different.

59:48.217 --> 59:50.619
So what are you
saying, ash?

59:53.590 --> 59:56.224
'Cause you lead
a pretty good life.

59:59.696 --> 01:00:00.829
I...

01:00:08.104 --> 01:00:09.838
And you know what, mark?

01:00:11.841 --> 01:00:13.241
Just once,

01:00:13.243 --> 01:00:16.378
I wish you would talk to me
like I'm your wife

01:00:16.380 --> 01:00:18.614
and not some customer,
okay?

01:00:19.816 --> 01:00:23.352
No clichs,
no number one rules,

01:00:23.354 --> 01:00:26.121
no whatever it takes,
just once.

01:00:35.064 --> 01:00:36.965
Yeah.

01:00:38.668 --> 01:00:39.668
You're right.

01:00:47.944 --> 01:00:48.944
Look--

01:00:50.680 --> 01:00:52.781
Hey, mark,

01:00:52.783 --> 01:00:54.650
just wanted
to let you know

01:00:54.652 --> 01:00:56.051
your dad's
looking for you.

01:01:06.062 --> 01:01:07.195
I...

01:01:11.401 --> 01:01:14.069
Malcolm, on P.A.:
Mark to my office.

01:01:15.071 --> 01:01:17.105
Mark to my office.

01:01:47.103 --> 01:01:49.104
When I page you,
it's for a reason.

01:01:49.106 --> 01:01:50.472
I was handling heat.

01:01:50.474 --> 01:01:51.840
I don't give a shit.
What about the 150 grand?

01:01:51.842 --> 01:01:53.041
Have you talked
to Russell?

01:01:53.043 --> 01:01:54.476
Yes. I spoke to him,
and we're good.

01:01:54.478 --> 01:01:56.411
He said he's personally
deposit it on Monday.

01:01:56.413 --> 01:01:58.180
And you were
gonna tell me when?

01:01:58.182 --> 01:01:59.414
For the holidays?
Maybe for my birthday?

01:01:59.416 --> 01:02:00.949
As a gift?
Put a bow on it?

01:02:00.951 --> 01:02:02.851
I'm telling you now!
For sure?

01:02:02.853 --> 01:02:04.086
Yes! He's one
of my best friends!

01:02:04.088 --> 01:02:05.454
He's a used-car
wholesaler.

01:02:05.456 --> 01:02:07.089
I give you my word.

01:02:07.091 --> 01:02:08.090
Your word?

01:02:09.392 --> 01:02:11.193
Good.

01:02:11.195 --> 01:02:13.729
And what about the car

01:02:13.731 --> 01:02:15.464
that Scott
gave away this morning?
The barretts?

01:02:15.466 --> 01:02:17.799
She's coming in an hour.
I'll handle it.

01:02:17.801 --> 01:02:19.267
Uh, you better.

01:02:19.269 --> 01:02:21.837
'Cause contrary
to what you think,

01:02:21.839 --> 01:02:24.139
this is not
a charitable organization.

01:02:24.141 --> 01:02:25.407
Now what about you?

01:02:25.409 --> 01:02:26.475
19 cars.

01:02:26.477 --> 01:02:27.809
19 cars.

01:02:27.811 --> 01:02:29.344
Better get back to work.

01:02:29.346 --> 01:02:31.179
Thank you.
You're welcome.

01:02:32.749 --> 01:02:34.449
Sheri, I assure you,
no one's trying

01:02:34.451 --> 01:02:36.118
to bait and switch you,
okay?

01:02:36.120 --> 01:02:39.020
But like I said,
I'd be more than happy

01:02:39.022 --> 01:02:41.490
